definition.value: An acetate salt with formula Pb(OAc)4. It is used as a selective oxidising agent in organic synthesis.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of (12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z)-triacontapentaenoic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (12Z,15Z,18Z,21Z,24Z)-triacontapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-acyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the 1-acyl group is specified as stearoyl (octadecanoyl).
An organic calcium salt that is the hemicalcium salt of rosuvastatin.
A multi-methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA(4-) oxanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of pristanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (25S)-3alpha,7alpha,12alpha-trihydroxy-5beta-cholestan-26-oyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-acyl-2-arachidonoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the 1-acyl group is also arachidonoyl.
A cardiolipin 72:4(2-) that is the dianion formed from tetraoleoyl cardiolipin by loss of an electron from each of the phospho groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-acyl-2-linoleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate in which the 1-acyl group is also linoleoyl.
An EC 3.4.24.* (metalloendopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of anthrax lethal factor endopeptidase (EC 3.4.24.83).
A 2,2'-dilysocardiolipin(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 1,1'-dioleyl 2,2'-dilysocardiolipin; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) oxanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of (2S)-2-methylpentadecanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate in which the acyl substituents at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and (4Z,7Z,10Z,13Z,16Z,19Z)-docosahexaenoyl respectively.
A 2-monolysocardiolipin(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of trioleoyl 2-monolysocardiolipin; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of benzimidazoles that is 1H-benzimidazole which is substituted by a [4-methoxy-3,5-dimethylpyridin-2-yl)methyl]sulfinyl group at position 2 and a methoxy group at position 5.
A carbohydrate sulfonate that is D-fructofuranose in which the hydroxy group at at position 6 is replaced by a sulfo group.
A 5-methoxy-2-{[(4-methoxy-3,5-dimethylpyridin-2-yl)methyl]sulfinyl}-1H-benzimidazole that has R configuration at the sulfur atom.
A carbohydrate sulfonate that is D-fructofuranose-1-phosphate in which the hydroxy group at at position 6 is replaced by a sulfo group.
An organic anion resulting from the deprotonation of the hydrogen-bearing nitrogen of the imidazole group of esomeprazole.
An alkanesulfonic acid  that is propanal carrying hydroxy and sulfo substituents at positions 2 and 3 respectively
An alkanesulfonic acid obtained by the formal substitution of one of the methyl hydrogens of propane-1,2-diol by a sulfonic acid group.
A methyl-branched fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of pristanic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A dTDP-sugar having beta-L-evernitrose as the sugar component.
A phytocannabinoid that is Delta(9)-tetrahydrocannabinol in which the methyl group at C-11 has been hydroxylated . Major metabolite of Delta(9)-tetrahydrocannabinol.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate  in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 1,3-diglyceride with acyl groups at positions 1 and 3 of sn-glycerol.

A phytocannabinoid that is Delta(9)-tetrahydrocannabinol in which the C-11 methyl has been fully oxidised to a carboxy group. Further enzymatic oxidation product of 11-hydroxy-Delta(9)-tetrahydrocannabinol.
A 1-alkyl-3-acylglycerol in which the glycerol moiety has sn stereochemistry.
A multi-methyl-branched fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of phosphate and diphosphate functions of (2R)-pristanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and arachidonoyl respectively.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4-phosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and oleoyl respectively.

An imidazothiazole that is imidazo[2,1-b][1,3]thiazole in which the double bonds at the 2-3 and 5-6 positions have been reduced to single bonds and in which one of the hydrogens at position 6 is replaced by a phenyl group.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 4,5-bisphosphate in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups at positions 1 and 2 are specified as stearoyl and oleoyl respectively.
An 8-carbon primary aliphatic amine.
A dTDP-sugar having 2,3,6-trideoxy-3-C-methyl-4-O-methyl-3-nitroso-beta-L-arabino-hexopyranose as the sugar component.
A dTDP-sugar having N-hydroxy-beta-L-evernosamine as the sugar component.
A 6-phenyl-2,3,5,6-tetrahydroimidazo[2,1-b][1,3]thiazole that has R configuration.
1-(alk-1-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of any 1-(Z)-alk-1-enyl-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A dTDP-sugar having beta-L-evernosamine as the sugar component.
A 1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-2-O-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkenyl group has Z geochemistry.
A 1-O-(alk-1-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkenyl group has Z geochemistry.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkenyl group has Z geochemistry.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of levamisole and dexamisole.

A member of the class of  dihydrochalcones that is dihydrochalcone substituted by a hydroxy group at position 2', methoxy groups at positions 4 and 4' and a hydroxy group at position alpha- to the ketonic group.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alkenyl group has Z geochemistry.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine zwitterion in which the alk-1-enyl group has Z geochemistry.
